The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to predict wind pressures around circular cylinders, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves regression analysis, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper involves image processing techniques to analyze the wind pressure data, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves the use of decision trees and gradient boosting regression trees, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE).
